  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Moreover, all the vessels which King Ahaz in his reign did cast away in his transgression,.... Not that he threw them away, being valuable, as made of gold and silver; but, as Kimchi interprets it, he removed them, and converted them to idolatrous uses; or, as the Targum, he defiled or profaned them, and made them abominable by strange idols: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "have we prepared and sanctified, and, behold, they are before the altar of the Lord; they had cleaned them, and fitted them for service, and had put them where they were ready for use; though the Targum is,\"we have laid them aside, and hid them, and prepared others in their room,''as unfit for divine service; and which is the sense of other Jewish writers (o). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(o) T. Bab. Avodah Zarah, fol. 54. 2.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(o) T. Bab. Avodah Zarah, fol. 54. 2.",
            "children": []
